      "blocks": {
        "faq_jXa7gP": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What Is a Hydrafacial Treatment?",
            "answer": "Hydrafacial treatments are non-invasive facial treatments that use patented Vortex-Fusion technology to cleanse, exfoliate, extract and hydrate the skin in a single session. It combines gentle suction with specialized HydroPeel® tips to remove impurities and dead skin cells while simultaneously infusing nourishing serums. <br><br>Unlike traditional facials, Hydrafacial treatments are designed as a multi-step system that improves overall skin health while addressing specific concerns such as dryness, congestion, uneven tone or fine lines.<br><br>Each Hydrafacial treatment can also be customized with boosters, LED light therapy and lymphatic drainage for a truly personalized experience."
          }
        },
        "faq_TWFwEm": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What Does a Hydrafacial Treatment Do?",
            "answer": "Hydrafacial treatments work by delivering multiple skin therapies at once. During treatment, the provider uses the <u><a href=\"https://www.hydrafacial.com/pages/the-device\">Hydrafacial device’s</a></u> wand attachment to gently remove dead skin cells, clear away impurities and infuse the skin with hydrating serums. The process helps improve texture, tone and radiance, while targeting issues like dryness, congestion, fine lines and uneven skin tone. The result is designed for refreshed, glowing skin that looks healthier and feels smoother immediately after the procedure.<br><br>The treatment follows a 7-step process, including cleansing, exfoliation, extractions, hydration and customized boosters, so skin receives comprehensive care in one session."
          }
        },
        "faq_9McTBL": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What Are the Benefits of a Hydrafacial Treatment?",
            "answer": "A Hydrafacial treatment provides both immediate glow and long-term improvements to skin health. It’s designed to deeply cleanse, exfoliate, extract impurities and hydrate in a single session. After just one visit, clients often notice a visible reduction in pore size, fine lines and uneven texture<sup>1,2</sup>, along with an increase in hydration<sup>1,2</sup>. <br><br>With regular sessions, Hydrafacial treatments can help improve the appearance of blemishes, refine tone and texture and support a stronger skin barrier. Many clients describe leaving with skin that looks brighter, smoother and more refreshed."
          }
        },
        "faq_qB8bcM": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What Are Hydrafacial Treatment Boosters?",
            "answer": "Boosters are targeted serums that personalize treatment. They’re formulated to address specific concerns, including dark spots, fine lines, redness or congestion and are delivered deep into the skin using Hydrafacial’s Vortex-Fusion technology. Adding boosters not only enhances results but can also increase the long-term benefits of treatments."
          }
        },
        "faq_qTagLq": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What Skin Conditions Can Hydrafacial Treatments Address?",
            "answer": "Hydrafacial treatments are customizable to target a wide range of <a href=\"https://www.hydrafacial.com/pages/skin-concerns\"><u>skin concerns</u></a>. They are commonly used to improve the look of fine lines and wrinkles, dullness, dryness and uneven tone or texture. The treatment is also effective in addressing congestion and clogged pores, reducing the visible effects of acne and blemishes and supporting more youthful-looking skin by improving elasticity and plumpness. <br><br>In addition to facial treatments, Hydrafacial offers Keravive™ therapy, which helps promote a healthier scalp and fuller-looking hair. This versatility makes Hydrafacial treatments suitable for nearly every skin type and concern."
          }
        },
        "faq_H4Mizh": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How Often Should People Get a Hydrafacial Treatment?",
            "answer": "The frequency of Hydrafacial treatments depends on the individual’s unique skin needs and goals. Many clients schedule sessions about once a month to maintain a consistent glow and optimal hydration, while others may find every 2-3 months works well for them. Because Hydrafacial is gentle and non-irritating, it can even be performed as often as every 1-2 weeks for those seeking more intensive results or ongoing maintenance.<br><br>Because a Hydrafacial treatment is customizable, providers can recommend the ideal cadence based on skin type, lifestyle and desired results. Consistent sessions can help extend results, keeping skin looking smooth, radiant and refreshed."
          }
        },
        "faq_9b3TBW": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How Much Is a Hydrafacial Treatment?",
            "answer": "The cost of a Hydrafacial treatment varies depending on the type of treatment, the provider’s pricing and if any add-ons or boosters are selected. On average, a Hydrafacial treatment typically starts around $199, with deluxe or platinum options priced higher. Since Hydrafacial treatments are available at thousands of clinic and medspa locations worldwide, it’s best for clients to check with a local provider for exact pricing."
          }
        },
        "faq_MjKjaY": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How Does Hydrafacial Compare to Microdermabrasion?",
            "answer": "Hydrafacial and microdermabrasion are both skin resurfacing treatments, but they work in very different ways. Microdermabrasion uses abrasive crystals or a diamond-tipped wand to mechanically exfoliate the skin, removing dead surface cells. While it can improve texture and tone, it may leave skin feeling dry or irritated, especially for those with sensitive skin.<br><br>Hydrafacial, on the other hand, uses patented Vortex-Fusion technology to cleanse, exfoliate and extract impurities while simultaneously infusing hydrating and nourishing serums. The process is gentle, non-invasive and customizable, making it suitable for nearly all skin types. Unlike microdermabrasion, Hydrafacial leaves skin feeling refreshed, plump and hydrated immediately after treatment."
          }
        },
        "faq_i96Cjn": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Where Can Providers Buy a Hydrafacial Machine?",
            "answer": "Hydrafacial devices are available exclusively through The Hydrafacial Company and its authorized representatives. Purchasing directly ensures that systems come with a valid trademark license, access to genuine consumables, training and warranty protection. Buying from unauthorized third-party resellers or the secondhand market risks access to critical benefits and may even void existing warranties.<br><br>If interested in purchasing a device, providers can connect with <a href=\"https://www.hydrafacial.com/pages/connect-with-sales\"><u>Hydrafacial’s sales team</u></a> to explore options. Availability and support extend across the United States and worldwide. <br><br>Providers can also meet with representatives in person at one of the <a href><u>major industry tradeshows</u></a> we attend across cities like Los Angeles, New York, Miami and Chicago. These events are a great opportunity to see the technology in action, ask questions and experience the results firsthand."
          }
        },
        "faq_mCz7Ne": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Are Third-Party Hydrafacial Devices Available for Purchase?",
            "answer": "No. <a href=\"https://www.hydrafacial.com/pages/device-authenticity\"><u>Authentic Hydrafacial devices</u></a> are only available directly through Hydrafacial and its authorized representatives. Buying from third-party resellers or the secondhand market puts providers at risk for outdated, damaged or modified equipment that lacks quality and warranty protection.<br><br>For providers looking to manage upfront costs, Hydrafacial also offers certified refurbished systems that meet the same quality standards as new devices. Each refurbished unit is fully inspected, licensed and backed by the same warranty and support, providing a safe, cost-effective way to join the Hydrafacial network. <br><br>Only devices purchased directly from Hydrafacial include: <br><br><ul>\n<li>-A valid trademark license to legally market services as Hydrafacial treatments</li> <li>-Access to genuine consumables, tips and boosters</li>\n<li>-Warranty protection, training and ongoing clinical support</li> <li>-Entry into Hydrafacial’s global provider network</li>\n</ul><br>For providers who purchase a device secondhand, they will be required to pay a $10,000 recertification fee for Hydrafacial to inspect, recertify and license the device before it can be used. Without this license, promoting Hydrafacial treatments or ordering consumables is not legal."
          }
        }
